Class Manager

  • java.lang.Object
    • usr.gustavo6046.pathman.Manager

  • public class Manager
extends java.lang.Object
    Author:
    gustavo6046 The PSM (Plan Space Manager) is an abstraction which goal is to ease the use of the key PathMan features, that are most likely to appear in AI projects or even simple games.

      • makeBaseCircumstance

        public BaseCircumstance makeBaseCircumstance(java.util.Optional<java.lang.String> key,
                                             java.util.Collection<Condition> conditions)
        Creates and registers a BaseCircumstance, i.e., a circumstance that has no special characteristics or inheritance whatsoever. Only use when you don't need Circumstance integration, or you do it by exporting the Circumstances instead of implementing them!
        Parameters:
        key - A key (if any) to label the new circumstance in the manager.
        conditions - The Conditions with which to create the new Circumstance. Prefer to use Condition.builder() to generate the list.
        Returns:
        The new Circumstance. It is automatically registered, so you don't need to Add it.

      • makeAction

        public Action makeAction(Circumstance.Matcher prerequisite,
                         Circumstance result,
                         double cost)
        Creates an Action and registers it.
        Parameters:
        prerequisite - The prerequisite Matcher with which Circumstances must match in order to connect outwardly to this Action.
        result - The Circumstance that results from "doing" this Action.
        cost - The Dijkstra base cost of doing this Action.
        Returns:
        The action made. It is automatically registered, so you don't need to Add it.

      • buildPlan

        public java.util.Optional<java.util.List<Action>> buildPlan(java.lang.String beginKey,
                                                            java.lang.String endKey)
                                                     throws java.lang.ClassNotFoundException,
                                                            java.security.KeyException
        Builds the final Action path, using the Path Space. This version uses a key String and supports only one goal Circumstance.
        Parameters:
        beginKey - The key of the first Circumstance.
        endKey - The key of the goal Circumstance.
        Returns:
        The list of Actions needed to reach the goal Circumstance, or Optional.empty() if it can't be reached.
        Throws:
        java.lang.ClassNotFoundException
        java.security.KeyException

                                                            java.security.KeyException
        Builds the final Action path, using the Path Space. This version uses a Matcher and supports multiple goal Circumstances.
        Parameters:

        goalMatcher - The Matcher with which match the goal Circumstances.
